<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Captured U.S. Correspondent Handed Over to Red Cross </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Captured U.S. Correspondent Handed Over to Red Cross </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0705172794 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0705172794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Affairs Ministry of the Islamic State of 
Afghanistan today handed over an American citizen who had 
entered Afghanistan illegally to a Red Cross representative in 
Kabul. According to a report by a BIA correspondent, Mrs. Maria 
Korolov who is a REUTER news agency reporter, had entered 
Afghanistan via Tajikistan. She was arrested by the security 
authorities in Kundoz and was transferred to Kabul. The Red 
Cross expressed appreciation for this humanitarian action 
carried out by the government of Afghanistan+. The Red Cross 
added that Mrs. Korolov will soon be leaving for her home 
country. 
  Meanwhile, the Foreign Affairs Ministry of the Islamic State 
of Afghanistan requested that all citizens of foreign countries, 
who intend to visit Afghanistan, obtain a visa through political 
representations of Afghanistan abroad and then enter 
Afghanistan. Otherwise, those who violate the law, will be dealt 
with in accordance with the current laws in the country. 

</TEXT>

